<paragraph id="31011E55B271FFD23CDD2CCC4CBACECF" blockId="9.[1000,1267,925,946]" box="[1000,1267,925,946]" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">
<heading id="6A49A939B271FFD23CDD2CCC4CBACECF" box="[1000,1267,925,946]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" reason="2">
NON 
<taxonomicName id="F6BE65D6B271FFD23B132CCC4CBACECF" authorityName="GOLDFUSS" authorityYear="1847" box="[1062,1267,925,946]" class="Amphibia" family="Actinodontidae" genus="Sclerocephalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Temnospondyli" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="03CAC247B271FFD23B132CCC4CBACECF" box="[1062,1267,925,946]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">SCLEROCEPHALUS</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="31011E55B271FFD23C0F2C924C83C96A" blockId="9.[826,1441,963,1903]" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">
In the course of the present study, we revisited the available evidence on two other taxa that were previously referred to 
<taxonomicName id="F6BE65D6B271FFD23B2F2B514C8AC96A" authorityName="GOLDFUSS" authorityYear="1847" box="[1050,1219,1024,1045]" class="Amphibia" family="Actinodontidae" genus="Sclerocephalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Temnospondyli" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="03CAC247B271FFD23B2F2B514C8AC96A" box="[1050,1219,1024,1045]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">Sclerocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="79A44DDEB271FFD23C662B4E4C59CA10" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="31011E55B271FFD23C662B4E4CCFC875" blockId="9.[826,1441,963,1903]" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">
<taxonomicName id="F6BE65D6B271FFD23C662B4E4D41C94B" authority="Fritsch, 1901" authorityName="Fritsch" authorityYear="1901" box="[851,1288,1055,1077]" class="Amphibia" family="Actinodontidae" genus="Sclerocephalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Temnospondyli" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="credneri">
<emphasis id="03CAC247B271FFD23C662B4E4C2BC94B" box="[851,1122,1055,1076]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">Sclerocephalus credneri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="552F63A4B271FFD23B592B4E4D41C94B" author="Fritsch A" box="[1132,1288,1055,1077]" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" refId="ref19941" refString="Fritsch A. 1901. Fauna der Gaskohle und der Kalksteine der Permformation Bohmens. Band IV, Heft 3. Prague (Selbstverlag)." type="book" year="1901">Fritsch, 1901</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. This species is based on poorly preserved material most recently revised by 
<bibRefCitation id="552F63A4B271FFD23CF52B0D4CDDC90D" author="Werneburg R" box="[960,1172,1116,1138]" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" pagination="343 - 355" refId="ref22016" refString="Werneburg R. 1993. Onchiodon (Eryopidae, Amphibia) aus dem Rotliegend des Innersudetischen Beckens (Bohmen). Palaontologische Zeitschrift 67: 343 - 355." type="journal article" year="1993">Werneburg (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, who referred it to 
<taxonomicName id="F6BE65D6B271FFD23AB22B0D4B98C9F0" authorityName="Geinitz" authorityYear="1861" class="Amphibia" family="Eryopidae" genus="Onchiodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Temnospondyli" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="labyrinthicus">
<emphasis id="03CAC247B271FFD23AB22B0D4B98C9F0" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">O. labyrinthicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. None of the autapomorphies of 
<taxonomicName id="F6BE65D6B271FFD23A662B2B4BD4C9D1" authorityName="GOLDFUSS" authorityYear="1847" class="Amphibia" family="Actinodontidae" genus="Sclerocephalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Temnospondyli" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="03CAC247B271FFD23A662B2B4BD4C9D1" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">Sclerocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are present in this material, whereas the shape of the interclavicle and the abbreviated posterior skull table indeed suggest closer relationships with 
<taxonomicName id="F6BE65D6B271FFD23C4D2BA44BBAC875" baseAuthorityName="Witzmann" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[888,1011,1269,1290]" class="Amphibia" family="Eryopidae" genus="Onchiodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Temnospondyli" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="03CAC247B271FFD23C4D2BA44BBAC875" box="[888,1011,1269,1290]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">Onchiodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F6BE65D6B271FFD23B042BA44C36C875" baseAuthorityName="Romer" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[1073,1151,1269,1290]" class="Amphibia" family="Eryopidae" genus="Eryops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Temnospondyli" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="03CAC247B271FFD23B042BA44C36C875" box="[1073,1151,1269,1290]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">Eryops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="31011E55B271FFD23C662A424C59CA10" blockId="9.[826,1441,963,1903]" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">
<taxonomicName id="F6BE65D6B271FFD23C662A424CB2C856" authority="(Gaudry, 1866)" baseAuthorityName="Gaudry" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[851,1275,1299,1321]" class="Amphibia" family="Eryopidae" genus="Onchiodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Temnospondyli" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="frossardi">
<emphasis id="03CAC247B271FFD23C662A424C76C857" box="[851,1087,1299,1320]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">Onchiodon frossardi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="552F63A4B271FFD23B672A424CBAC856" author="Gaudry A" box="[1106,1267,1299,1321]" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" pagination="340 - 341" refId="ref19967" refString="Gaudry A. 1866. Sur le reptile trouve par M. Frossard dans les schistes bitumineux de Muse, pres d'Autun (saone-et- Loire). Comptes Rendus Academie des Sciences Paris 63: 340 - 341." type="journal article" year="1866">Gaudry, 1866</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Described by 
<bibRefCitation id="552F63A4B271FFD23C0F2A634BACC837" author="Gaudry A" box="[826,997,1330,1352]" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref20006" refString="Gaudry A. 1887. L' Actinodon. Nouvelles Archives Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle 10: 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1887">Gaudry (1887)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="552F63A4B271FFD23CC02A634CFCC837" author="Thevenin A" box="[1013,1205,1330,1352]" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" pagination="1 - 65" refId="ref21932" refString="Thevenin A. 1910. Les plus anciens quadrupedes de. France. Annales de Paleontologie 5: 1 - 65." type="journal article" year="1910">Thevenin (1910)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="552F63A4B271FFD23BCE2A634DD4C837" author="Heyler D" box="[1275,1437,1330,1352]" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" pagination="42 - 51" refId="ref20139" refString="Heyler D. 1966. Sur le genre Actinodon et autres stegocephales de l'Autunien de France. Revue Sciences Bourbonnais Centre France 1966: 42 - 51." type="journal article" year="1966">Heyler (1966)</bibRefCitation>
. Part of the classic material from the French Autun Basin, including the 
<typeStatus id="EE05A0F7B271FFD23B0B2A3E4CD6C8FA" box="[1086,1183,1391,1413]" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="F6BE65D6B271FFD23BE42A214D29C8FB" baseAuthorityName="Gaudry" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[1233,1376,1391,1413]" class="Amphibia" family="Eryopidae" genus="Onchiodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Temnospondyli" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="frossardi">
<emphasis id="03CAC247B271FFD23BE42A214D29C8FB" box="[1233,1376,1391,1413]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">O. frossardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was recently revised by 
<bibRefCitation id="552F63A4B271FFD23B2E2ADF4CA1C8DB" author="Werneburg R" box="[1051,1256,1422,1444]" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" pagination="167 - 181" refId="ref22045" refString="Werneburg R. 1997. Der Eryopide Onchiodon (Amphibia) aus dem Rotliegend des Beckens von Autun (Frankreich). Freiberger Forschungshefte C: 167 - 181." type="book chapter" year="1997">Werneburg (1997)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="552F63A4B271FFD23A162ADF4BBFC8BC" author="Werneburg R &amp; Steyer JS" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" pagination="599 - 607" refId="ref22147" refString="Werneburg R, Steyer JS. 1999. Redescription of the holotype of Actinodon frossardi (Amphibia, Temnospondyli) from the Lower Permian of the Autun Basin (France). Geobios 32: 599 - 607." type="journal article" year="1999">Werneburg &amp; Steyer (1999)</bibRefCitation>
. As suggested earlier by 
<bibRefCitation id="552F63A4B271FFD23A2B2AFC4DD4C8BC" author="Boy JA" box="[1310,1437,1453,1475]" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" pagination="107 - 132" refId="ref19270" refString="Boy JA. 1988. Uber einige Vertreter der Eryopoidea (Amphibia: Temnospondyli) aus dem europaischen Rotliegend (? hochstes Karbon - Perm). 1. Sclerocephalus. Palaontologische Zeitschrift 62: 107 - 132." type="journal article" year="1988">Boy (1988)</bibRefCitation>
, the broad-skulled specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="49A95EC5B271FFD23BC82A9A4D05C89F" box="[1277,1356,1483,1504]" name="France" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">France</collectingCountry>
share various features with eryopids (see phylogenetic analysis), but none with 
<taxonomicName id="F6BE65D6B271FFD23B4029594D57CB62" authorityName="GOLDFUSS" authorityYear="1847" box="[1141,1310,1544,1565]" class="Amphibia" family="Actinodontidae" genus="Sclerocephalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Temnospondyli" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="03CAC247B271FFD23B4029594D57CB62" box="[1141,1310,1544,1565]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">Sclerocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or stereospondylomorphs. In the light of our new evidence on 
<taxonomicName id="F6BE65D6B271FFD23C0F29144BAACB25" authorityName="GOLDFUSS" authorityYear="1847" box="[826,995,1605,1626]" class="Amphibia" family="Actinodontidae" genus="Sclerocephalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Temnospondyli" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="03CAC247B271FFD23C0F29144BAACB25" box="[826,995,1605,1626]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">Sclerocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, there are no grounds to include 
<taxonomicName id="F6BE65D6B271FFD23AB229174BE9CB06" baseAuthorityName="Gaudry" baseAuthorityYear="1866" class="Amphibia" family="Eryopidae" genus="Onchiodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Temnospondyli" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="frossardi">
<emphasis id="03CAC247B271FFD23AB229174BE9CB06" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">O. frossardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="F6BE65D6B271FFD23CF029354C27CB06" authorityName="GOLDFUSS" authorityYear="1847" box="[965,1134,1636,1657]" class="Amphibia" family="Actinodontidae" genus="Sclerocephalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Temnospondyli" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="03CAC247B271FFD23CF029354C27CB06" box="[965,1134,1636,1657]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">Sclerocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as suggested by 
<bibRefCitation id="552F63A4B271FFD23A0329354B95CBE6" author="Schoch RR &amp; Milner AR" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" pagination="203" refId="ref21526" refString="Schoch RR, Milner AR. 2000. Stereospondyli. In: Wellnhofer P, ed. Handbuch der Palaoherpetologie vol. 3 B. Munich: Pfeil, 203." type="book chapter" year="2000">Schoch &amp; Milner (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. In the present study, we refer to this taxon as 
<taxonomicName id="F6BE65D6B271FFD23C9929F34C70CBC9" baseAuthorityName="Gaudry" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[940,1081,1697,1719]" class="Amphibia" family="Eryopidae" genus="Onchiodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Temnospondyli" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="frossardi">
<emphasis id="03CAC247B271FFD23C9929F34C70CBC9" box="[940,1081,1697,1719]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">O. frossardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as was proposed by the last revisors, 
<bibRefCitation id="552F63A4B271FFD23C9729914C95CBA9" author="Werneburg R &amp; Steyer JS" box="[930,1244,1728,1750]" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" pagination="599 - 607" refId="ref22147" refString="Werneburg R, Steyer JS. 1999. Redescription of the holotype of Actinodon frossardi (Amphibia, Temnospondyli) from the Lower Permian of the Autun Basin (France). Geobios 32: 599 - 607." type="journal article" year="1999">Werneburg &amp; Steyer (1999)</bibRefCitation>
. We do so despite the fact that our phylogenetic analysis (below) does not find 
<taxonomicName id="F6BE65D6B271FFD23C9429AC4C65CA6D" baseAuthorityName="Gaudry" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[929,1068,1789,1810]" class="Amphibia" family="Eryopidae" genus="Onchiodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Temnospondyli" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="frossardi">
<emphasis id="03CAC247B271FFD23C9429AC4C65CA6D" box="[929,1068,1789,1810]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">O. frossardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F6BE65D6B271FFD23B5929AC4D6ECA6D" authorityName="Geinitz" authorityYear="1861" box="[1132,1319,1789,1810]" class="Amphibia" family="Eryopidae" genus="Onchiodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Temnospondyli" pageId="9" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="labyrinthicus">
<emphasis id="03CAC247B271FFD23B5929AC4D6ECA6D" box="[1132,1319,1789,1810]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="144">O. labyrinthicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to form a clade, because we want to leave nomenclatorial changes to future, more detailed studies of eryopid intrarelationships.
</paragraph>
